<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 1:19PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT EAST CENTRAL MIFFLIN...CENTRAL
JUNIATA AND CENTRAL PERRY COUNTIES THROUGH 145 PM EDT...
At 119 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lewistown, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lewistown, Burnham, Highland Park, Yeagertown, Spruce Hill, Juniata
Terrace, Mexico, Alfarata, Ickesburg, Walnut, Mifflintown, Port
Royal, Mifflin and Maitland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
